# Node Editing

## Plan

- Click node → inline edit popover (textarea, auto-focused)
- Save on blur or Enter
- Escape closes popover
- Delete node via button or keyboard
---
- Voice input via Web Speech API (Stage 4)

## Built

### Stage 1 (2026-03-27)
- `NodePopover.tsx` — floating edit popover, textarea auto-focused on open
- Save on blur or Enter, Escape closes

### Post-Stage 2 Polish (2026-03-28)

**Bug fixes:**
- Ghost node bug: `onSave` firing on blur after discard was writing empty nodes to DB. Fixed with `discardedRef` — a Set that marks node IDs as discarded before any save can fire
- Popover re-opening bug: `setSelectedNode(saved)` after temp node save re-opened popover. Changed to `setSelectedNode(null)`
- Double node creation on blur: clicking away fired both `onSave` (blur) and `onNodeCreate` (canvas click). Fixed by setting `suppressNextCreateRef.current = true` at top of `onSave`

**Keyboard shortcuts:**
- `Enter` — saves and closes
- `Escape` — discards if empty, closes
- `Tab` on empty node — moves node right by `tabIndentX`
- `Shift+Tab` — moves node left by `tabIndentX`
- `Tab` on filled node — saves current node, creates child at `(x + tabIndentX, calcDynamicY(text))` with explicit edge
- `Shift+Enter` — saves current node, creates new node below at `(x, calcDynamicY(text))` with explicit edge
- `Shift+Arrow` — repositions current node in arrow direction using `tabIndentX` (left/right) and `shiftEnterIndentY` (up/down); works on empty or filled nodes; does not save or create
- `Delete`/`Backspace` — deletes all selected nodes when selection active and no textarea focused
- Tab/Shift+Enter await `onSave` before calling `onNodeCreateFromEdge` so real node ID is used as edge source
- `onSave` returns `Promise<string>` (real node ID after DB write)

**Other:**
- "Select subtree" button in popover triggers BFS subtree selection
- Delete button in popover with immediate confirm
- `calcDynamicY(text)` — computes child Y as `node.y + Math.ceil(text.length / wrapLength) * defaultSize + shiftEnterIndentY`


### Image Nodes + R2 Upload (2026-04-09)
- `src/lib/isImageUrl.ts` — detects image URLs by extension or known host (imgur, unsplash, wikimedia, *.r2.dev)
- `Canvas.tsx` allNodes.each: if isImageUrl(d.text), early-return if `<image>` already present (flicker fix), else load via `window.Image()` for natural dimensions, render at x=12 y=4 with clipPath rounded corners
- `NodePopover.tsx` — paste handler compresses images before upload using browser Canvas API (max 1200px wide, image/webp at 0.85 quality), then POSTs to /api/upload, sets node text to R2 URL, shows uploading/error state
- `src/app/api/upload/route.ts` — POST endpoint, auth-guarded, uploads to R2 via S3Client, returns { url }
- `src/app/api/nodes/[id]/route.ts` — DELETE handler now calls DeleteObjectCommand to clean up R2 objects when an image node is deleted

